						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone window in the left outer wall of the temple of Śabari (Sōravva) in a valley about two miles from the village.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1089-90.</p>						

						<p>This record, in Sanskrit language and Nāgari characters, is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1031 Śukla, Vaisākha,</hi> the other details being lost. The cyclic year corresponded to <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1011 (A.D. 1089-90).</hi> The details are insufficient for verification.</p>						

						<p>The inscription records the commencement of the car festival on the specified date.</p>						

						</summary>
